100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On January 12, 1926, the League of Nations convened in Geneva, addressing ongoing tensions in Europe and the need for disarmament. In the United States, the Senate debated a new immigration bill aimed at restricting entries from certain countries, stirring controversy among lawmakers. Meanwhile, in Germany, economic struggles continued as the Weimar Republic faced inflationary pressures, prompting calls for reform.
